title: Trump Schmoozing With Manufacturing CEOs And Forcing One To Tell Trump’s Hole-In-One Story Is Hilarious
text:
Trump just made Jeff Immelt describe the time Trump hit a hole-in-one 
Trump: “I actually said I was the best golfer of all the rich people” pic.twitter.com/6yB7oj6WJe 
— Bradd Jaffy (@BraddJaffy) February 23, 2017 CEO: I'm "Denise Morrison, from the Campbell Soup Company" 
Trump: "Good soup." pic.twitter.com/ynW7dwmYe9 
— Steve Kopack (@SteveKopack) February 23, 2017 Trump to CEO of Caterpillar construction equipment company: "The Caterpillars are the best" pic.twitter.com/YwYM8Yrt8I 
— Steve Kopack (@SteveKopack) February 23, 2017 
God damn these just crack me up. The Donald shooting the shit with manufacturing’s elite. “Campbells? Good soup. Caterpillar? Love the D-10. Is that Jeff from GE? Jeff tell ‘em my hole-in-one story.” 
Nobody schmoozes better than Donnie schmoozes. Half-expected Samsung to introduce themselves and get a “Love Samsung. That Galaxy Note 7? Fire phone, absolute fire” from Trump. 
Just another ridiculous yet fun and interesting day in Trump’s America. Riggs |
